The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, June 25, 2004 				 CM sermon to out-of-sync party
																								Siliguri, June 24: The chief minister today told the CPMs Darjeeling secretariat members to stop squabbling and instead concentrate on bridging their divide with people.																								Buddhadeb Bhattacharjees advice comes when the party seems to have fallen out of favour with a large section of tea garden workers and is grappling with growing rift between its hills and plains units.																								Bhattacharjee, who presided over a closed-door party meeting today, is learnt to have asked members about the nature of contacts local leaders cultivate at the grassroots level.
